"Section",ExpressionUUID->"3925dc3d-b31b-4ac2-ba6a-ba7066f5ad22"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "FindBounce is a Mathematica package that computes the bounce configuration \
needed to compute \nthe false vacuum decay rate with multiple scalar fields. \
The physics background is described in the \npaper by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  ButtonBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Guada", ",", 
     RowBox[{"Maiezza", " ", "and", " ", "Nemev\[SHacek]ek"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"(", "2019", ")"}]}],
   BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
   ButtonData->{
     URL["https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.02227"], None},
   ButtonNote->"https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.02227"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "db1257a8-6348-4249-b4d4-286277fa7a84"],
 ". In this tutorial, we present examples of false vacuum decays in potential \
with multiple scalar fields.\n\nThe notebook cannot be saved, so it can be \
edited freely. Contributions are welcome! "
}], "Text", \
"ApplicationNotes",ExpressionUUID->"b4c990ac-e483-4a37-aade-b78176e68ca6"],

